OL,3,CCelebrations in Rory's hometown with
OL,4,Cback-to-back win in Masters
OL,6,FEighteen-year-old Ollie Keown came
OL,7,Fover from Scotland under the guise of
OL,8,Frevising for exams, but somehow found
OL,9,Ftime to cheer on McIlroy.
OL,11,FHe said this year's victory was better
OL,12,Fthan 2025, which he said made him
OL,13,F"more nervous".
OL,15,FHe said: "I'm just amazed, stunned ` I
OL,16,Floved every second of it."
OL,18,FOn returning to Scotland, he said:
OL,19,F"We'll see how long the celebrations
OL,20,Flast."
OL,26,@uD@AOUuD@NO]wD@JOUxD@ZO]{D@AOU|D@FO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G6/9
